race.comment: FAST TRACK (6) fifth-up for this and has the speed to get across from the awkward gate. Ran into the minor money again after sitting on the speed when a narrow third over this track and trip. Adept in all conditions and surely another win is imminent. ELIVINA (9) underrated mare kept fresh for this. Just over a month between runs when a disappointing fifth as fav over 1600m at Nowra. Kept up to the mark with an1150m trial placing at this course and will relish the sting out of the ground. Each-way. MICHELANGELO (7) sharp win first-up over the unsuitable trip at Wyong, then didn't appreciate the tongue control bit when a poor seventh over 1550m at Canterbury. Ordered to the trials when given a 1050m tick over trial. No shock to see him return to winning form. VALIANT BOMB (8) back sharply in grade deep into the prep. Struck a bit of trouble early when a fading eighth over 1550m at Canterbury in BM64 grade. Expected to bounce back here.
